Articles.Content: dammit out of likes again. So yay! Thanks!

1 hour ago, Kermanzooming said:

The one and only mod I really can't live without. 

Thanks @TriggerAu!

It really is. #1 imo. 

How on Kerbin this isn't a stock feature yet is the most astoundingly mind-boggling oversight in over 4 years of KSP (and i love KSP to bits). If the devs are worried about making the early game too easy, just slot it into the last upgrade of the mission control centre. It needs to be stock to help encourage the younger/newcomer/thicker (delete where applicable, i fall under thicker) players to attempt to venture beyond the mun and minmus when you first play it.

Edited October 12, 2016 by Stevie_D
missed out a word, i did mention i fall under "thicker"
@TriggerAu, awesome! The OP has today's date, but still leads with "1.1.x" FYI, I assume it should say 1.2. Once again, thanks!

1 hour ago, tater said:

@TriggerAu, awesome! The OP has today's date, but still leads with "1.1.x" FYI, I assume it should say 1.2. Once again, thanks!

The GitHub has the latest version for 1.2 the other two links are for 1.1.3.
@TriggerAu You're faster then Light! Thank you!

On 9/28/2016 at 9:15 PM, steve_v said:

Don't poke the bears modders. It will be done when it's done. 1.2 hasn't even been released yet anyway.
NB. repeated requests for updates are also forbidden by forum rules.

In the mean time, you could use this.

Ok. Sorry.

KSP 1.2 has been released yesterday ... sorry

It's based on pre-release 1586

Updated the two text mistakes, and yep the other sources will get updated when they add 1.2 as a version of KSP, for now its just github

The speed of this update is really down to @JPLRepo and @nightingale providing Pull requests so I just had to double check and test - couldnt have been anywhere near ready withouth their work
So happy to see the Ol' TriggerTech folder in my GameData directory again Thanks for getting this out so quickly!

seems Gihuib is kinda stinky with me .. unsure if thats just me but i cannot download v3.8 via GitHub (i might just need to give it time to chill from the storm of downloads .. it says it cant reach "github-cloud.s3.amazonaws.com" .. maybe a cloud issue from GitHub) works perfectly now

BUT! very cool mod indeed and ty for the quick update!

Edited October 13, 2016 by LatiMacciato

Feature Request:

Accept decimals in the year field.
Due to the new communications system I would like to put a set of relays around Kerbol.  To facilitate this I would like to be able to set alarms at .25, .5 and .75 years.  Nothing urgent, I will be doing it manually before an update is likely, but the feature would be nice to have if it's not too much work.

Many thanks for updating this most vital mod.

Cheers and thanks to all who worked / work on this mod.

I guess absence makes the heart grow stronger because I had forgotten how much I rely on KAC after playing for a while without it. 

 

Many thanks for this mod, really grateful for it.
Thanks a lot for the update. I think this mod is one of the essentials, can't believe this functionality is still not part of the game, together with KER's.
TRIGGER!!!!!!!!! Thank you and bless you, sir!  I've been holding off 1.2 just because I couldn't bear to play without this. Your work means THAT much!

First I want to say thank you. This is a required mod for me. I cannot play the game, the way I like, without it. It totally changed KSP for me when I first used it many moons ago. I was happy to find it is still being developed when I picked up KSP again recently.

Second, I am getting intermittent (often) crashes to desktop, using the 'jump to ship' button. This could be caused by my laptop. KSP works it hard. But it's not a behaviour I saw pre 1.2 and pre 3.8.0.0. This is not a big issue for me. I can just go through the tracking station or map screen. But being a new release I thought you would want to know.
Ill have a look at the jump to ship thing on the weekend as well

2 hours ago, Eddiedigits said:

Second, I am getting intermittent (often) crashes to desktop, using the 'jump to ship' button

Me too. Usually switching from a ship to another. It doesn't happen often, but when it does, it's usually 'persistent, meaning that if I reload the game after it has crashed and then try to 'jump to ship' from the same situation it caused the previous crash, it crashes again. To solve this, going back to Space Center before switching ship fixes it.

If useful, I could provide a log of the crashes. Error.log says 'access violation': "Write to location 19930522 caused an access violation.": it's the same in all crashes.
